    <item>
      <title>The Way of Learning</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/The-Way-of-Learning/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 19 Dec 2022 08:33:00 +0530</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/The-Way-of-Learning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5208-The-Way-of-Learning.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;The Way of Learning &#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The Way of Learning 
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-way-of-learning&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#the-way-of-learning&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to teach your children the process of making tea &lt;br&gt;
then you don&amp;rsquo;t force them to memorize s for sugar, &lt;br&gt;
g for ginger, t for tea, w for water, m for milk, b for boil, etc. &lt;br&gt;
And if they don&amp;rsquo;t memorize you punish them? &lt;br&gt;
You don&amp;rsquo;t offer them tea? &lt;br&gt;
You don&amp;rsquo;t allow them to come into the kitchen till they remember the complete vocabulary? &lt;br&gt;
If this is your way of teaching then it is horrible, &lt;br&gt;
Children don&amp;rsquo;t need any jail or hell &lt;br&gt;
You are Yamraj and they are living in hell.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
